parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag can cause unexpected deployment, leading to injuries, accidents, or total loss of the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbag deployment without impact or collision
excessive heat warning
higher-than-average humidity
auditory injuries due to high-decibel explosion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in receiving recall notifications and repairs can leave vehicles unsafe to drive, putting occupants at risk.
symptoms: Failure to receive recall notifications
unavailability of parts
delayed repairs
lack of communication from manufacturers and dealerships.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump failure can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle not starting
burned fuel pump.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent push-to-start failure can cause the vehicle to be unable to start, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially causing safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences intermittent push-to-start failures
multiple unknown warning lights illuminate on the instrument panel
and the vehicle requires several attempts to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The door lock malfunction can cause the doors to unlock or open unexpectedly while driving, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The doors lock and unlock on their own
the doors fly open while driving
and the vehicle's electrical system is affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Stalling and Electrical System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle stalling and electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to shut off while in motion, leading to accidents or injuries, and can also cause damage to the vehicle's electrical system.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while in motion
all lights on the dashboard flash
the ABS brake light is the most dominant issue
and the vehicle will not start for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the steering wheel abruptly jerks or violently turns to one side
the steering wheel is difficult or impossible to turn in one direction
the vehicle is difficult to control or steer.
